.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt TERMSCOPE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm termscope
.Nd headless terminal emulator for programmatic TUI interaction
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm snapshot
.Op Fl -format Ar fmt
.Op Fl o Ar path
.Op Fl -cols Ar N
.Op Fl -rows Ar N
.Op Fl -wait-idle Ar ms
.Fl - Ar cmd Op Ar args ...
.Nm
.Cm exec
.Op Fl -wait-for-text Ar pattern
.Op Fl -type Ar text
.Op Fl -press Ar key
.Op Fl -wait-idle Ar ms
.Op Fl -snapshot
.Op Fl -expect Ar text
.Op Fl -timeout Ar ms
.Fl - Ar cmd Op Ar args ...
.Nm
.Cm session
.Op Fl -cols Ar N
.Op Fl -rows Ar N
.Fl - Ar cmd Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
spawns a command in a virtual terminal powered by libghostty-vt,
allowing programmatic interaction and state capture.
It is designed for AI agents, CI pipelines, and TUI testing.
.Pp
Three subcommands are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Cm snapshot
Launch a command, wait for output to settle, capture the terminal
state, and print it to stdout.
.It Cm exec
Launch a command and execute a linear sequence of actions specified
by flags, processed left to right.
.It Cm session
Launch a command and enter an interactive JSON-lines protocol session,
reading requests from stdin and writing responses to stdout.
See
.Xr termscope-session 7
for the protocol specification.
.El
.Sh GLOBAL OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl -cols Ar N
Terminal width in cells.
Default: inherited from parent TTY, or 80.
.It Fl -rows Ar N
Terminal height in cells.
Default: inherited from parent TTY, or 24.
.It Fl -term Ar VALUE
TERM environment variable for the child.
Default:
.Dq xterm-256color .
.It Fl -theme Ar dark|light
Color theme.
Default:
.Dq dark .
.It Fl -env Ar KEY=VALUE
Set an environment variable for the child process.
May be specified multiple times.
.It Fl -inherit-env
Inherit the full parent environment instead of a curated subset.
.It Fl -version
Print version and exit.
.It Fl -help
Print usage and exit.
.El
.Sh SNAPSHOT OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl -format Ar fmt
Output format:
.Dq text
(default),
.Dq spans ,
.Dq json ,
.Dq html ,
.Dq svg .
.It Fl o Ar path
Write output to a file instead of stdout.
.It Fl -wait-idle Ar ms
Milliseconds of idle time before capturing.
Default: 200.
.El
.Sh EXEC OPTIONS
Processed left to right as a linear sequence of steps:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl -wait-for-text Ar pattern
Block until
.Ar pattern
appears on the terminal screen.
.It Fl -type Ar text
Send
.Ar text
as keyboard input.
.It Fl -press Ar key
Send a key using Emacs notation.
See
.Sx KEY NOTATION .
.It Fl -wait-idle Ar ms
Wait for output to settle.
.It Fl -snapshot
Capture and print the terminal state.
.It Fl -expect Ar text
Assert
.Ar text
is present.
Exit 0 if found, 1 if not.
.It Fl -timeout Ar ms
Set timeout for subsequent wait operations.
Default: 30000.
.El
.Sh KEY NOTATION
.Nm
uses Emacs-style key notation:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "C-M-a" -compact
.It C-c
Ctrl+C
.It M-x
Alt+X
.It C-M-a
Ctrl+Alt+A
.It RET
Enter
.It TAB
Tab
.It ESC
Escape
.It SPC
Space
.It DEL
Backspace
.It <up> <down> <left> <right>
Arrow keys
.It <home> <end>
Home/End
.It <prior> <next>
Page Up/Down
.It <f1> ... <f12>
Function keys
.El
.Pp
Key sequences are space-separated:
.Dq C-x C-s
means press Ctrl+X, then Ctrl+S.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ev TERM
Set to
.Fl -term
value (default
.Dq xterm-256color ) .
.It Ev COLORTERM
Set to
.Dq truecolor .
.It Ev TERM_PROGRAM
Set to
.Dq termscope .
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Pp
For
.Cm exec
with
.Fl -expect ,
exits 0 if the text is found, 1 if not.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Snapshot a TUI:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
termscope snapshot -- htop
.Ed
.Pp
JSON snapshot with custom size:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
termscope snapshot --format json --cols 120 --rows 40 -- btop
.Ed
.Pp
Interactive sequence:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
termscope exec \\
  --wait-for-text "Search:" \\
  --type "hello" \\
  --press RET \\
  --snapshot \\
  -- my-tui
.Ed
.Pp
CI assertion:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
termscope exec --expect "Error" -- my-app || echo "Error found"
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr termscope-session 7
